  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5509",
  "title": "Impossible to negate a value with connectToggleFilter",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nWhen we are using connectToggleFilter, the `on/off `values are escaped so we can not pass minus sign to invoke a negation filtering.\r\nFor example, my value is '-0' because I want all results that do not match facet value '0'.\r\n\r\nSee : https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/f802fd0f56d7e898c85e947fa6a3e5c11ff1b6ec/packages/instantsearch.js/src/connectors/toggle-refinement/connectToggleRefinement.ts#L194\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Go on the codesandbox\r\n2. Click on the \"Brand\" Toggle\r\n3. Nothing is displayed\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/weathered-meadow-9yw8p7?file=/src/App.tsx\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nAll brand are displayed except 'Apple'\n\n### Package version\n\nreact-instantsearch-hooks-web 6.32.0\n\n### Operating system\n\nWindows 10\n\n### Browser\n\nChrome 110\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
